        <section class="page__content" itemprop="text">
          <p>Considering the worldwide boom of mobile apps and that Spain is one of the European countries with more mobile app users, this course, organised by Fundaci√≥n Telef√≥nica, offered the possibility to gain knowledge and make a way in a laboral market with various opportunities to these professionals.</p>
          <p>The participants learnt Android and iOS, became familiar with JAVA language like Objective C and learnt how to access from the apps to all functionalities of the terminal, as well as to publish the apps on Apple and Google repositories to be downloaded.</p>
          <p>The course had a four month duration divided into a core training on app architecture, web design, web design with Phone Gap and JAVA programming. Another specific part on app developing for Android, iOS and project developing, as well as a skills part to improve the personal brand, job seeking 2.0 and enhance professional competencies.</p>
          <br />
          <p>Teaching iOS app developing. During the project the participants were divided into teams of 5-6 and together with a collaborating company, developed an app that they would present at a event. In this part of the course I monitored and guided the groups so as to help them finish their projects in iOS and Android.</p>
